wikimedia-lvs-realserver (0.04) edgy; urgency=low

  * Use a config script instead of debconf prompting in postinst
  * Remove quotes in if-down, which causes errors if no LVS IPs are bound.
  * Set a default LVS_SERVICE_IPS value (Apaches LVS IP)

 -- Mark Bergsma <mark@wikimedia.org>  Sun, 13 May 2007 18:09:11 +0000

wikimedia-lvs-realserver (0.03) edgy; urgency=low

  * 'test' in Edgy doesn't seem to like operator '==', use '=' instead
  * 'ip' in Edgy doesn't seem to like ip addr del without a /32 mask
  * Use Linux's IP address "labels" to tag LVS addresses and reliably
    remove them

 -- Mark Bergsma <mark@wikimedia.org>  Sun,  5 Nov 2006 15:39:03 +0000

